1. From BUMP HDIAG outputs
- plot_cmat_diag_rh.py
	: plot the "raw" sample correlation and "fitted" function for horizontal lengths
- plot_cmat_diag_rv.py
	: plot the "raw" sample correlation and "fitted" function for vertical lengths

- plot_cmpr_cmat_rh.py
	: compare the vertical profiles of horizontal lengths between current adn benchmark experiments
- plot_cmpr_cmat_rv.py
	: compare the vertical profiles of vertical lengths between current adn benchmark experiments
- plot_cmpr_var_stddev.py
	: compare the vertical profiles of error standard deviations betweencurrent adn benchmark experiments

2. From BUMP NICAS outputs
- plot_nicas_grids.ncl
	: plot the full and halos (SA, SB, SC) grid

3. From BUMP VBAL outputs
- plot_vbal_regcoef.ncl
	: plot the diagnosed regression coefficients
- plot_vbal_explained_variance.ncl
	: plot the explained variance from regression
